# Implement Memory Backend

In-memory storage backend for testing and ephemeral operations.

## Implementation

```typescript
class MemoryBackend implements StorageBackend {
  readonly structured: StructuredStores;
  readonly delta: DeltaApi;
  readonly serialization: SerializationApi;

  readonly capabilities: BackendCapabilities = {
    nativeBlobDeltas: true,
    randomAccess: true,
    atomicBatch: false,
    nativeGitFormat: false,
  };

  constructor() {
    const blobMap = new Map<ObjectId, Uint8Array>();
    const treeMap = new Map<ObjectId, TreeEntry[]>();
    const commitMap = new Map<ObjectId, Commit>();
    const tagMap = new Map<ObjectId, Tag>();
    const refMap = new Map<string, Ref>();
    const deltaMap = new Map<ObjectId, { baseId: ObjectId; delta: Uint8Array }>();

    this.structured = {
      blobs: new MemoryBlobStore(blobMap, deltaMap),
      trees: new MemoryTreeStore(treeMap),
      commits: new MemoryCommitStore(commitMap),
      tags: new MemoryTagStore(tagMap),
      refs: new MemoryRefStore(refMap),
    };

    this.delta = new MemoryDeltaApi(blobMap, deltaMap);
    this.serialization = new MemorySerializationApi(this.structured, this.delta);
  }
}
```

## Characteristics

- **Fast**: No I/O, all in-memory
- **Ephemeral**: Data lost on close
- **Testing**: Primary use case
- **Reference implementation**: Simplest backend to understand

