# Implement PackBuilder

Incremental pack file builder with delta support.

## Interface

```typescript
interface PackBuilder {
  /**
   * Add object (engine decides full vs delta)
   */
  addObject(id: ObjectId): Promise<void>;

  /**
   * Add object with explicit delta preference
   */
  addObjectWithDelta(
    id: ObjectId,
    preferredBaseId?: ObjectId
  ): Promise<void>;

  /**
   * Finalize and get pack stream
   */
  finalize(): AsyncIterable<Uint8Array>;

  /**
   * Get current pack statistics
   */
  getStats(): PackBuildStats;
}

interface PackBuildStats {
  totalObjects: number;
  deltifiedObjects: number;
  totalSize: number;
  deltaSavings: number;
}

interface PackOptions {
  useDelta?: boolean;
  thinPack?: boolean;
  maxChainDepth?: number;
  onProgress?: (stats: PackBuildStats) => void;
}
```

## Pack File Format

```
PACK header (12 bytes):
  - "PACK" magic (4 bytes)
  - Version 2 (4 bytes)
  - Object count (4 bytes)

Objects (variable):
  - Type + size (varint encoded)
  - Content or delta

Trailer:
  - SHA-1 checksum (20 bytes)
```

## Delta Types in Pack

- **OFS_DELTA**: Offset to base object in same pack
- **REF_DELTA**: SHA-1 of base object (thin packs)

## Key Design

Wire format can use deltas for ALL object types (Git compatibility), even though internal storage only tracks blob deltas.

