# Implement SerializationApi - Loose Objects

Git-compatible loose object serialization and parsing.

## Interface Subset

```typescript
interface SerializationApi {
  /**
   * Serialize an object to Git loose format
   * Produces: zlib(type + " " + size + "\0" + content)
   */
  serializeLooseObject(id: ObjectId): AsyncIterable<Uint8Array>;

  /**
   * Parse Git loose format into internal representation
   */
  parseLooseObject(
    compressed: AsyncIterable<Uint8Array>
  ): Promise<{ id: ObjectId; type: ObjectType }>;

  /**
   * Export single object in Git format
   */
  exportObject(id: ObjectId): Promise<{
    type: ObjectType;
    content: AsyncIterable<Uint8Array>;
  }>;

  /**
   * Import single object from Git format
   */
  importObject(
    type: ObjectType,
    content: AsyncIterable<Uint8Array>
  ): Promise<ObjectId>;
}
```

## Git Loose Object Format

```
zlib_compress(
  "{type} {size}\0{content}"
)
```

Example for a blob:
```
zlib_compress("blob 12\0Hello World!")
```

## Streaming Implementation

```typescript
async *serializeLooseObject(id: ObjectId): AsyncGenerator<Uint8Array> {
  const meta = await this.getObjectMeta(id);
  yield* compressStream(
    prependStream(
      encodeHeader(meta.type, meta.size),
      this.structured.blobs.loadBlob(id)
    )
  );
}
```

