Checkout the first commit version using VCS Checkout command.

## Purpose

Demonstrate VCS checkout capability by materializing the first commit's state to the working directory. This tests:
1. Checkout command works after GC
2. Delta resolution during checkout
3. Tree traversal and blob extraction

## Implementation

```typescript
import { CheckoutCommand } from '@webrun-vcs/core';

// Get the first commit ID (stored during step 03)
const firstCommitId = context.firstCommitId;

// Create checkout command
const checkout = new CheckoutCommand(repository, workingCopy);

// Checkout the first commit
const result = await checkout.checkout(firstCommitId, {
  force: true,  // Override any local changes
  onProgress: (progress) => {
    console.log(`Checkout: ${progress.current}/${progress.total} files`);
  },
});

console.log('Checkout Results:');
console.log(`  Files updated: ${result.updated.length}`);
console.log(`  Files added: ${result.added.length}`);
console.log(`  Files removed: ${result.removed.length}`);
console.log(`  Conflicts: ${result.conflicted.length}`);

// List files that were checked out
console.log('\nFiles in working directory:');
for (const file of result.updated.concat(result.added)) {
  console.log(`  ${file}`);
}
```

## Verification

After checkout, verify:
1. Working directory contains only files from first commit
2. File contents match the original blobs
3. No extra files from later commits
4. Directory structure matches first commit's tree

```typescript
// Verify file contents match first commit
const firstCommit = await repository.commits.loadCommit(firstCommitId);
const tree = await repository.trees.loadTree(firstCommit.tree);

for await (const entry of walkTree(repository.trees, firstCommit.tree)) {
  const expectedContent = await collectBytes(repository.blobs.load(entry.objectId));
  const actualPath = path.join(REPO_DIR, entry.path);
  const actualContent = await fs.readFile(actualPath);

  assert(
    Buffer.compare(expectedContent, actualContent) === 0,
    `Content mismatch: ${entry.path}`
  );
}
