Verify repository validity using native git commands.

## Purpose

After VCS-native GC, verify the repository is still valid from native git's perspective. This ensures VCS operations maintain Git compatibility.

## Native Git Commands to Run

```typescript
import { execSync } from 'node:child_process';

function runGitCommand(cmd: string, cwd: string): string {
  try {
    return execSync(cmd, { cwd, encoding: 'utf-8', stdio: 'pipe' });
  } catch (error) {
    throw new Error(`Git command failed: ${cmd}\n${error.stderr}`);
  }
}

// 1. Full repository integrity check
const fsckOutput = runGitCommand('git fsck --full --strict', REPO_DIR);
console.log('git fsck --full --strict:');
console.log(fsckOutput || '  (no errors)');

// 2. Verify all commits are readable
const logOutput = runGitCommand('git log --oneline', REPO_DIR);
console.log('\ngit log --oneline:');
console.log(logOutput);

// 3. Verify HEAD commit details
const showOutput = runGitCommand('git show HEAD --stat', REPO_DIR);
console.log('\ngit show HEAD --stat:');
console.log(showOutput);

// 4. Verify ref integrity
const showRefOutput = runGitCommand('git show-ref', REPO_DIR);
console.log('\ngit show-ref:');
console.log(showRefOutput);

// 5. Count objects from git's perspective
const countOutput = runGitCommand('git count-objects -v', REPO_DIR);
console.log('\ngit count-objects -v:');
console.log(countOutput);
```

## Verification Checks

1. git fsck --full --strict
   - Should complete with no errors
   - Verifies object connectivity and integrity

2. git log --oneline
   - Should show all 20 commits
   - Verifies commit chain is intact

3. git show HEAD
   - Should display latest commit details
   - Verifies tree and blob access

4. git show-ref
   - Should show refs/heads/main pointing to HEAD
   - Verifies ref storage

5. git count-objects -v
   - Reports object counts and sizes
   - Compare with VCS counts

